      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think this filter is a common idea, and slightly tricky to implement, and so we should offer it as a \u0027feature\u0027. If we decide internally that we choose to impl it using sksl, that\u0027s fine, but I suspect that maybe can\u0027t happen (for chrome) until we\u0027re sure they can jit everywhere they might use this.\n\nBrian, we chatted about this a while ago. Do you have other thoughts?",
      "parentUuid": "f0da8c2c_876dd27c",
      "revId": "10ae9934d6566234aad0b6f1b663264fe8083bce",
