      "writtenOn": "2020-07-17T12:19:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m not talking about sksl or runtime effects.\n\nI\u0027m totally fine offering bicubic as a Skia feature.  It\u0027s just that if we reimplement it, it would be nice  to make it work for any shader.\n\nI wouldn\u0027t worry about Chrome and JITing.  I think it\u0027s totally reasonable for us to ignore maximum performance on machines without GPUs until Chrome asks us to turn on a JIT.  This wouldn\u0027t be a regression... it\u0027d be a slow new feature.",
      "parentUuid": "95e52910_ed3c6f46",
      "revId": "10ae9934d6566234aad0b6f1b663264fe8083bce",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
