      "writtenOn": "2020-07-17T13:10:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I almost made the same point about pulling this out of image and having it take a shader. However, it really is a way to interpolate between samples (pixels for an image) on a regular 2D grid. And I couldn\u0027t think of another example of an input shader that fits that description. But maybe I wasn\u0027t being creative enough. I suppose a user could do something like a manual version of yuv planar image and using multiple image shaders and then want to bicubic that. Or blend between two same sized images and then bicubic that... \n\nI see no harm in pulling it out, in general think we should have simple orthogonal building blocks rather than compound effects, and maybe it\u0027s even useful to someone.",
      "parentUuid": "f0efa770_832623cd",
      "revId": "10ae9934d6566234aad0b6f1b663264fe8083bce",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
