      "writtenOn": "2020-07-17T13:22:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, I think we might be surprised how many ideas like this might pop up with that mechanism in place.  One particular area I think could benefit from filtering is hard-stop gradients, e.g. https://codepen.io/chriscoyier/pen/csgoD.  They end up with an ugly unantialiased edge, but sampled through a bilerp or bicubic wrapper the hard edge would stay in place geometrically but look a little nicer.",
      "parentUuid": "2ef494bb_8a4e51bc",
      "revId": "10ae9934d6566234aad0b6f1b663264fe8083bce",
